        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1813299260" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12446370575235077424">Phew!! I struggled from the start to finish, and am glad that it is over. I didn&apos;t like it. Unlike the first two books which were centered around the characters and their struggles, this was about Catholics and Protestants, two decade long fight between Elizabeth and Mary for the throne. <br/><br/>The first two books were more about the characters and their strife to survive each day. I elated in their small victories, felt sad in their pain, but here I didn&apos;t connect with the characters. Reading this fel</span>
  <span id="freeText12446370575235077424" style="display:none">Phew!! I struggled from the start to finish, and am glad that it is over. I didn't like it. Unlike the first two books which were centered around the characters and their struggles, this was about Catholics and Protestants, two decade long fight between Elizabeth and Mary for the throne. <br /><br />The first two books were more about the characters and their strife to survive each day. I elated in their small victories, felt sad in their pain, but here I didn't connect with the characters. Reading this felt like I was reading about the battles that took place between England and France in late 1500. <br /><br />I guess I was expecting something as exciting as the first two books but I was very disappointed in this story. </span>
