<span id="freeTextContainer17341397035642867992">&apos;A Column of Fire&apos; by Ken Follett. I loved &apos;Pillars of the Earth&apos; and &apos;World Without End&apos; so I had high hopes for this book but I think I was put off by the fact that I had read a lot of historical books about this period so it was rather boring to me. I did engage with a couple of the characters and found parts of the book interesting. </span>
  <span id="freeText17341397035642867992" style="display:none">'A Column of Fire' by Ken Follett. I loved 'Pillars of the Earth' and 'World Without End' so I had high hopes for this book but I think I was put off by the fact that I had read a lot of historical books about this period so it was rather boring to me. I did engage with a couple of the characters and found parts of the book interesting. </span>
