<div id="review_3741658913" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3741658913" />
    <a title="Karl Jorgenson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12413321-karl-jorgenson"><img alt="Karl Jorgenson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1584120483p2/12413321.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3741658913?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karl Jorgenson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karl Jorgenson" href="/user/show/12413321-karl-jorgenson">Karl Jorgenson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3741658913" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11143413050256130727">It takes a long time to slog through 900 pages, an estimated 400,000 words, but it&apos;s worth it. For the third book in this medieval series, we jump forward to the 16th century. Across France, Spain, and England, Catholics and Protestants are looking for ways to kill everybody who doesn&apos;t agree with them, royal aspirants are planning to slip the dagger to their rivals, and greed, lust, and envy drive the society. Awesome. As usual with Follett&apos;s historical epics, we follow several characters from </span>
  <span id="freeText11143413050256130727" style="display:none">It takes a long time to slog through 900 pages, an estimated 400,000 words, but it's worth it. For the third book in this medieval series, we jump forward to the 16th century. Across France, Spain, and England, Catholics and Protestants are looking for ways to kill everybody who doesn't agree with them, royal aspirants are planning to slip the dagger to their rivals, and greed, lust, and envy drive the society. Awesome. As usual with Follett's historical epics, we follow several characters from their young-adulthood as they mature, become important, and participate in the big events of the era. As a descendent of new-world colonists, I was shockingly unaware of this period of European history, so who became king or queen was a surprise to me. I'm sure the characters' stories are a delight, even to those readers who know who Henri II is.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11143413050256130727" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


