    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2121940856" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2121940856" />
    <a title="Tanja Berg" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5935491-tanja-berg"><img alt="Tanja Berg" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1558953813p2/5935491.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2121940856?book_show_action=true">Sep 26, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tanja Berg" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tanja Berg" href="/user/show/5935491-tanja-berg">Tanja Berg</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5935491-tanja-berg?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2121940856" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16058232814216393527">I expect sumptuous historical novels from Ken Follett and he definitely delivered again. The cast of villains and heroes is vast. This time the setting is time of Elizabeth I. She inherited the throne from her catholic sister Mary, much to the chagrin of the English Catholics. They would much rather have had a Catholic Queen, and many set their eyes on Mary, Queen of Scots. <br/><br/>The main character of this book is Ned Willard. He is in love with Margery, but her parents have intended her for someone e</span>
  <span id="freeText16058232814216393527" style="display:none">I expect sumptuous historical novels from Ken Follett and he definitely delivered again. The cast of villains and heroes is vast. This time the setting is time of Elizabeth I. She inherited the throne from her catholic sister Mary, much to the chagrin of the English Catholics. They would much rather have had a Catholic Queen, and many set their eyes on Mary, Queen of Scots. <br /><br />The main character of this book is Ned Willard. He is in love with Margery, but her parents have intended her for someone else. Ned is drawn into the network around Elizabeth and becomes a spy, infiltrating the networks that would have her de-throned. Ned's enarmoured with Elizabeth from the beginning, and particularly into her relgious tolerance. Traitors must die though, and there are plenty of those.<br /><br />This is a truly sprawling historical novel, that delves deeply into polar opposites of Mary, Queen of Scots, and Elizabeth I. I learned quite a bit of history. I thought Mary Queen of Scots perhaps was Elizabeth's half sister or something - given that Henry VIII, her father, had such a lot of wives - but no, she was just a distant cousin. <br /><br />This was as deeply satisfying a novel as any by Ken Follett that I have read, despite the fact that it took me almost two weeks to read it. He is definitely one of my favorite authors in the historical fiction genre. Absolutely recommended!<br /><br />There is no need to worry about this being #3 in a series, it can be read as a stand alone without missing any serious points at all. Although the previous two do deserve to be read, there is no particular need to read read them in order, they are that far removed in time from each other.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16058232814216393527" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

